Uses of Package
io.honeycomb.libhoney

  • Packages that use io.honeycomb.libhoney 
    Package Description
    io.honeycomb.libhoney
    Classes that define the public API; see the 'examples' module for simple use-cases.
    io.honeycomb.libhoney.eventdata
    Event internals.
    io.honeycomb.libhoney.responses
    Classes that define different types of responses that can be received for a submitted event.
    io.honeycomb.libhoney.responses.impl  
    io.honeycomb.libhoney.transport.impl  
  • Classes in io.honeycomb.libhoney used by io.honeycomb.libhoney 
    Class Description
    Event
    An Event holds data to be sent to Honeycomb.
    EventFactory
    This is used to generate Events with a shared set of properties.
    EventFactory.Builder
    Helper class to construct an EventFactory.
    EventPostProcessor
    Applies post-processing to events being submitted to Honeycomb.
    HoneyClient
    The Honeycomb Client
    Metrics
    Records measurements of elapsed time (in nanoseconds) for an event that has been submitted to the HoneyClient.
    Options
    Holds configuration options for HoneyClient, as well as their default values.
    Options.Builder
    Helper class to construct Options.
    ResponseObserver
    If registered with HoneyClient.addResponseObserver(ResponseObserver), this is the interface that will be notified about the outcome of events being sent through the client.
    TransportOptions
    Holds configuration options for the transport layer HoneyClient, as well as their default values.
    TransportOptions.Builder
    Helper class to construct TransportOptions.
    ValueSupplier
    Interface to supply field values dynamically.
